# cat-fountain

ATmega328P firmware for a cat water fountain. Controls a DC pump via a MOSFET
module and monitors water level with a float switch.

## Hardware

| Component    | Detail                         |
| ------------ | ------------------------------ |
| MCU          | ATmega328P @ 8 MHz (ext. XTAL) |
| Pump driver  | IRF520 MOSFET module           |
| Pump PWM pin | OC1A — PB1                     |
| Float sensor | PD2 (INPUT_PULLUP)             |
| Programmer   | USBasp via avrdude             |

### Float sensor wiring

```
Float switch leg A → GND
Float switch leg B → PD2 (uses internal pull-up)

Float UP   (water present) → switch OPEN  → PD2 reads HIGH
Float DOWN (tank empty)    → switch CLOSED → PD2 reads LOW
```

## Project layout

```
cat-fountain/
├── Makefile            ← top-level: build image, compile, flash
├── docker/
│   └── Dockerfile      ← Alpine image with avr-gcc toolchain
└── src/
    ├── Makefile        ← inner Makefile (runs inside the container)
    └── main.cpp        ← firmware source
```

## Workflow

### 1. Build the Docker image (once)

```sh
make build
```

### 2. Compile firmware

```sh
make compile
# output: build/cat-fountain.hex + build/cat-fountain.elf
```

### 3. Flash to MCU (avrdude must be installed on host)

```sh
make flash
```

Or flash manually:

```sh
avrdude -c usbasp -p atmega328p -P usb \
        -U flash:w:build/cat-fountain.hex:i
```

> **Important — fuse bits:** the firmware assumes an external 8 MHz crystal.
> Make sure your fuses are set accordingly, e.g.:
>
> ```sh
> avrdude -c usbasp -p atmega328p -P usb \
>         -U lfuse:w:0xFF:m -U hfuse:w:0xD9:m
> ```
>
> (CKSEL=1111, SUT=11 → full-swing crystal; CKDIV8 cleared)

## Pump control logic

- **PWM**: Timer1 Fast-PWM ~500 Hz, duty driven by `pump::RUN_PERCENT` (default 40 %).
- **Soft-start**: every time the pump is enabled it runs at 100 % for 800 ms to
  ensure the impeller starts, then drops to the operating duty.
- **Water level hysteresis**:
  - Pump **stops** after 20 consecutive "empty" reads (~200 ms).
  - Pump **restarts** only after 60 consecutive "full" reads (~600 ms).
  - This prevents rapid on/off cycling when the float is near the threshold.
- **Failsafe watchdog**: WDT @ 1 s — resets the MCU if the main loop stalls.
